Whether you're a gentle sprite at the edge of people's vision or a leathery little thing stealing their children to live a feral lifestyle, you hover at the edge of the possible world, waiting your opportunity. You know the wee folk hold the real power.

answersResultList.title: Mermaid.
answersResultList.resultContent: Skeptics assume you're a manatee or dolphin, but you're way more attractive. You swim like a fish, sing like an angel (perhaps fallen), and whip up deadly storms when sailors displease you. Yet people think sighting you is good luck - go figure. Maybe you don't always envy those who live on land, but you have a thing about stealing their hearts.

answersResultList.title: Phoenix.
answersResultList.resultContent: You're quick to reach your flashpoint, but you always come back good as new. You like intense colors, frequently hang with royalty or its equivalent, and are supposedly centuries old (as a reward for doing something good a long time ago). Every culture in the world has stories about you, so it's a safe bet that you get around.

answersResultList.title: Dragon.
answersResultList.resultContent: You're wise and fierce, divining the schemes of others, breathing fire when aroused. People fear you, but it's born out of respect. (You do have a constellation named after you.) Saints, gods, and heroes are always out to get you - in ritualized battle, like pro wrestling, to please the masses. You're smart enough to avoid actual fights.

answersResultList.title: Elf.
answersResultList.resultContent: Your backstory is conflicted, so you're either revered as a pagan god or shunned as a sexual threat. You might even be a creature of intense grace and infinite beauty. (And would that be so bad?) In truth, you probably have your own likeminded community that goes about its business hidden from the meddling, fearful world of humans.

answersResultList.title: Centaur.

Despite your voracious lower appetites, you're considered wise and noble (if a bit odd looking) and know a lot about the stars and planets. You also own twice as many shoes as most other people.
